RecordTypeDescription: Events from the Exchange admin audit log.
Events from an Exchange mailbox audit log for actions that are performed on a single item, such as creating or receiving an email message.
Events from an Exchange mailbox audit log for actions that can be performed on multiple items, such as moving or deleted one or more email messages.
Azure Active Directory OrgId logon events (deprecating).
Data loss protection (DLP) events in SharePoint and OneDrive for Business.
Events from the Sway service and clients.
Data loss protection (DLP) events in Exchange, when configured via Unified DLP Policy. DLP events based on Exchange Transport Rules are not supported.
Secure Token Service (STS) logon events in Azure Active Directory.
Admin actions from the Security & Compliance Center.
Events for eDiscovery activities performed by running content searches and managing eDiscovery cases in the Security & Compliance Center.
Phishing and malware events from Exchange Online Protection and Office 365 Advanced Threat Protection.
Submission events from Exchange Online Protection and Office 365 Advanced Threat Protection.
Microsoft Power Automate (formerly called Microsoft Flow) events.
Events related to DLP classification in SharePoint.
Events related to retention policies and retention labels in the Security & Compliance Center
Safe links time-of-block and block override events from Office 365 Advanced Threat Protection.
Events related to insights and reports in the Office 365 security and compliance center.
Phishing and malware events for files in SharePoint, OneDrive for Business, and Microsoft Teams from Office 365 Advanced Threat Protection.
Events related to the Patients application in Microsoft Teams for Healthcare.
